<P>And so well, Sirs, do I wish to your Voyages, that I would Entreat you, that for the <HI>Man<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ing of your Vessels</HI> in this Evil Time, there may be no such <HI>Un|fair Methods</HI> used, as may Entail Disasters <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">pon them.</P>
<P>There is one sort of <HI>Trade</HI> also, a|bout which my way of Addressing you, shall be by Reciting the words of the Excellent BAXTER. They are these; [His <HI>Christian Directory.</HI> Part II. Chap. 14&punc;]</P>
<P><Q>To go as <HI>Pirates,</HI> and Catch up poor <HI>N<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">groes,</HI> or People of another Land, that have never forfeited Life, or Liberty, and to make them <HI>Slaves,</HI>
