<P><HI>Fidelity</HI> to the cause of <HI>Righteousness,</HI> obliges me, to take Notice of One thing more.</P>
<P>If there be any <HI>English</HI> People, who are concerned with our <HI>Christianized Indians,</HI> but then take advantage of their <HI>Ignorance,</HI> or their <HI>Indigence,</HI> or their unchristian <HI>Love of the Bottel,</HI> to decoy them into their <HI>Debt;</HI> and then use In|direct and Oppressive wayes, to Exact an <HI>Unreasonable Satisfaction</HI> from them, and <HI>Sell</HI> them for Servants, or <HI>Send</HI> them out of their own Country; This Trade, will be a Reproach to our <HI>Christianity,</HI> and I am sure, it will be <HI>Bitterness in the Latter End.</HI> Certainly, our <HI>Iustices</HI> will concern themselves to Rebuke and Prevent such Doings, lest the Guilt become so <HI>Publick,</HI> as to provoke the Justice of Heaven to Re|venge it, by <HI>Indian</HI> Depredations.</P>
