<P>Instead of Propounding <HI>Laws,</HI> to retrench a Mischief, not easy to come at&punc; My Proposal is; That this One <HI>Observation</HI> may be Spred thro' the Country, and awfully consi|dered of. Tho' this Liquor may be <HI>Useful,</HI> at some time, &amp; in some things, yet <HI>no Man that uses it con|stantly will ever be Good for very much.</HI> It will infallibly <HI>Stunt</HI> his Abilities; He will discharge no <HI>Office,</HI> as he ought to do; It will <HI>Besot</HI> him, or, at least very much <HI>Flatten</HI> him, and make him very little better, than a meer <HI>Good for nothing.</HI> Take him from the <HI>Bottel,</HI> for the STATE, or for the CHURCH, or for the FIELD, <GAP DESC="illegible" REASON="faint" EXTENT="1 word"> be a <HI>Poor Tool;</HI> God will do little by him; hee'l never be <HI>Ex|cellent.</HI> When a man stands a <HI>Candi|date</HI> for any <HI>Preferment,</HI> I move, <HI>That it may be known, whether he be a Friend of
